    <PrimAttribute name="chargeZero" id="238a3ac7-e231-4283-9859-891730e00d3d">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>

Whether to create  zero quantity invoice lines. 

If you have specified the 'MappingType' to be single and the transaction maps to the second range e.g. 6-10, do you want a 1-5  line created?</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="mappingType" id="5388a48d-e85f-4615-b9ac-ac8397b6a1c4">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>

Single (MapType_Single = 0) or Escalating (MapType_Escalate = 1)

'Single' means map to the line whose quantity range the quantity falls into. 
	e.g. quantity of 9, ranges 1-5, 6-10, 11-15:  '9' encompasses only the second range. 
'Escalating' means map to each of the invoice lines that matches my quantity.
	e.g. quantity of 9, ranges 1-5, 6-10, 11-15:  '9' encompasses the first 2 ranges. </text>
    </PrimAttribute>
